  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cyclone Idai Response Phase 2 - Eagles</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Goal: To reduce vulnerability to the impact of disasters among flood-affected households in Chikwawa by strengthening disaster risk management systems and enhancing livelihoods.

- Farming households receive extension services and farm inputs to support them produce high value crops such as sesame and beans. Two solar-powered irrigation sites will be rehabilitated. Households supported with small livestock production. Linkages to markets are facilitated. 
- 100 young people aged 15-24 and 50 people with disability will be placed on an apprenticeship programme to train them in various vocational skills, which will increase the participants&#x2019; prospects for employment, earn income and contribute to reduction of various vulnerabilities. 
- Targeted farming households, young people and people with disability will have access to grants for non-agricultural livelihoods so that they can be empowered economically
- Communities will be oriented in early warning systems and communication mechanisms. Communities will also be trained on how to make small scale flood mechanisms on rivers. This will ensure that flood mitigation measures are undertaken at community level and communities have knowledge on these flood mitigation measures.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Outcomes: 
A) Vulnerable households have reduced their susceptibility to the impact of disasters through improved livelihood activities that increase household income
B) Young people and 100 people with disability have appropriate vocation and entrepreneurship skills to enable them increase employment prospects and earn income 
C) Livelihood groups from disaster-affected communities have access to unconditional grants to allow them take advantage of economic opportunities
D) Households have knowledge, skills and resources in early warning systems to deal with disaster risks
E) Target communities have access to safe, secure and user-friendly feedback and complaints mechanisms and able to get responses.</narrative>
  </description>
